<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-18T20:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-18T20:41:00-05:00" n="1537" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1537">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/60.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-18T19:00:00-06:41">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your July 16, 5 p.m. General Natera, Governor of Zacatecas, at
                                present in Monterey disclaims any knowledge of death and persecution
                                of Christian Brothers. States that Villa would know of the facts <pb facs="0988" n="872" xml:id="pg_872"/> in the case. Have made
                                verbal and written representation to Governor Carranza in the
                                matter. Welfare of Christian Brothers at Saltillo reported to
                                Department yesterday.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>